The KZN floods wreaked havoc. Hundreds lost their lives and key infrastructure was completely damaged and washed away. Tongaat residents haven’t had water for over a month and that will remain their reality for months to come. The deputy mayor of eThekwini says they are doing all they can. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos was with the deputy mayor of eThekwini to assess the damage. #DStv403 TONGAAT - Residents of Tongaat are desperate to have running water again. But the reality of that happening is not any time soon. READ: KZN Floods | Durban beaches closed after E.coli discovery The water plant was completely damaged during the floods and the project will take some time to complete. The sewage problem remains one of the biggest headaches for the metro. READ: KZN floods | Several beaches face extended closures Sewage pipes were damaged and that is now running into the rivers and ocean. * eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports.